20 /** Does the first expression have the same structure as the second?
21  * Variables in the first expression with the name * are interpreted
22  * as wildcards, and their matching equivalent in the second
23  * expression is placed in the vector give as the third argument.
24  * Wildcards require the types to match. For the type bits and width,
25  * a 0 indicates "match anything". So an Int(8, 0) will match 8-bit
26  * integer vectors of any width (including scalars), and a UInt(0, 0)
27  * will match any unsigned integer type.
28  *
29  * For example:
30  \code
31  Expr x = Variable::make(Int(32), "*");
32  match(x + x, 3 + (2*k), result)
33  \endcode
34  * should return true, and set result[0] to 3 and
35  * result[1] to 2*k.
36  */
37 bool expr_match(const Expr &pattern, const Expr &expr, std::vector<Expr> &result);
38 
39 /** Does the first expression have the same structure as the second?
40  * Variables are matched consistently. The first time a variable is
41  * matched, it assumes the value of the matching part of the second
42  * expression. Subsequent matches must be equal to the first match.
43  *
44  * For example:
45  \code
46  Var x("x"), y("y");
47  match(x*(x + y), a*(a + b), result)
48  \endcode
49  * should return true, and set result["x"] = a, and result["y"] = b.
50  */
51 bool expr_match(const Expr &pattern, const Expr &expr, std::map<std::string, Expr> &result);

55 /** An alternative template-metaprogramming approach to expression
56  * matching. Potentially more efficient. We lift the expression
57  * pattern into a type, and then use force-inlined functions to
58  * generate efficient matching and reconstruction code for any
59  * pattern. Pattern elements are either one of the classes in the
60  * namespace IRMatcher, or are non-null Exprs (represented as
61  * BaseExprNode &).
62  *
63  * Pattern elements that are fully specified by their pattern can be
64  * built into an expression using the make method. Some patterns,
65  * such as a broadcast that matches any number of lanes, don't have
66  * enough information to recreate an Expr.
67  */

145 inline HALIDE_NEVER_INLINE Expr make_const_special_expr(halide_type_t ty) {
146  const uint16_t flags = ty.lanes & MatcherState::special_values_mask;
147  ty.lanes &= ~MatcherState::special_values_mask;
148  if (flags & MatcherState::signed_integer_overflow) {
149  return make_signed_integer_overflow(ty);
150  }
151  // unreachable
152  return Expr();
153 }

155 HALIDE_ALWAYS_INLINE
156 Expr make_const_expr(halide_scalar_value_t val, halide_type_t ty) {
157  halide_type_t scalar_type = ty;
158  if (scalar_type.lanes & MatcherState::special_values_mask) {
159  return make_const_special_expr(scalar_type);
160  }
161 
162  const int lanes = scalar_type.lanes;
163  scalar_type.lanes = 1;
164 
165  Expr e;
166  switch (scalar_type.code) {
167  case halide_type_int:
168  e = IntImm::make(scalar_type, val.u.i64);
169  break;
170  case halide_type_uint:
171  e = UIntImm::make(scalar_type, val.u.u64);
172  break;
173  case halide_type_float:
174  case halide_type_bfloat:
175  e = FloatImm::make(scalar_type, val.u.f64);
176  break;
177  default:
178  // Unreachable
179  return Expr();
180  }
181  if (lanes > 1) {
182  e = Broadcast::make(e, lanes);
183  }
184  return e;
185 }

189 // A fast version of expression equality that assumes a well-typed non-null expression tree.
190 HALIDE_ALWAYS_INLINE
191 bool equal(const BaseExprNode &a, const BaseExprNode &b) noexcept {
192  // Early out
193  return (&a == &b) ||
194  ((a.type == b.type) &&
195  (a.node_type == b.node_type) &&
196  equal_helper(a, b));
197 }

230 template<int i>
231 struct WildConstInt {
232  struct pattern_tag {};
233 
234  constexpr static uint32_t binds = 1 << i;
235 
236  constexpr static IRNodeType min_node_type = IRNodeType::IntImm;
237  constexpr static IRNodeType max_node_type = IRNodeType::IntImm;
238  constexpr static bool canonical = true;
239 
240  template<uint32_t bound>
241  HALIDE_ALWAYS_INLINE bool match(const BaseExprNode &e, MatcherState &state) const noexcept {
242  static_assert(i >= 0 && i < max_wild, "Wild with out-of-range index");
243  const BaseExprNode *op = &e;
244  if (op->node_type == IRNodeType::Broadcast) {
245  op = ((const Broadcast *)op)->value.get();
246  }
247  if (op->node_type != IRNodeType::IntImm) {
248  return false;
249  }
250  int64_t value = ((const IntImm *)op)->value;
251  if (bound & binds) {
252  halide_scalar_value_t val;
253  halide_type_t type;
254  state.get_bound_const(i, val, type);
255  return e.type == type && value == val.u.i64;
256  }
257  state.set_bound_const(i, value, e.type);
258  return true;
259  }
260 
261  template<uint32_t bound>
262  HALIDE_ALWAYS_INLINE bool match(int64_t value, MatcherState &state) const noexcept {
263  static_assert(i >= 0 && i < max_wild, "Wild with out-of-range index");
264  if (bound & binds) {
265  halide_scalar_value_t val;
266  halide_type_t type;
267  state.get_bound_const(i, val, type);
268  return type == i64_type && value == val.u.i64;
269  }
270  state.set_bound_const(i, value, i64_type);
271  return true;
272  }

485  constexpr static bool foldable = true;
486  HALIDE_ALWAYS_INLINE
487  void make_folded_const(halide_scalar_value_t &val, halide_type_t &ty, MatcherState &state) const noexcept {
488  const auto *e = state.get_binding(i);
489  ty = e->type;
490  switch (e->node_type) {
491  case IRNodeType::UIntImm:
492  val.u.u64 = ((const UIntImm *)e)->value;
493  return;
494  case IRNodeType::IntImm:
495  val.u.i64 = ((const IntImm *)e)->value;
496  return;
497  case IRNodeType::FloatImm:
498  val.u.f64 = ((const FloatImm *)e)->value;
499  return;
500  default:
501  // The function is noexcept, so silent failure. You
502  // shouldn't be calling this if you haven't already
503  // checked it's going to be a constant (e.g. with
504  // is_const, or because you manually bound a constant Expr
505  // to the state).
506  val.u.u64 = 0;
507  }
508  }

529  HALIDE_ALWAYS_INLINE

534  template<uint32_t bound>
535  HALIDE_ALWAYS_INLINE bool match(const BaseExprNode &e, MatcherState &state) const noexcept {
536  const BaseExprNode *op = &e;
537  if (e.node_type == IRNodeType::Broadcast) {
538  op = ((const Broadcast *)op)->value.get();
539  }
540  switch (op->node_type) {
541  case IRNodeType::IntImm:

543  case IRNodeType::UIntImm:

545  case IRNodeType::FloatImm:

547  default:
548  return false;
549  }

664  constexpr static uint32_t binds = bindings<A>::mask | bindings<B>::mask;
665 
666  constexpr static IRNodeType min_node_type = Op::_node_type;
667  constexpr static IRNodeType max_node_type = Op::_node_type;
668 
669  // For commutative bin ops, we expect the weaker IR node type on
670  // the right. That is, for the rule to be canonical it must be
671  // possible that A is at least as strong as B.
672  constexpr static bool canonical =
673  A::canonical && B::canonical && (!commutative(Op::_node_type) || (A::max_node_type >= B::min_node_type));
674 
675  template<uint32_t bound>
676  HALIDE_ALWAYS_INLINE bool match(const BaseExprNode &e, MatcherState &state) const noexcept {
677  if (e.node_type != Op::_node_type) {
678  return false;
679  }
680  const Op &op = (const Op &)e;
681  return (a.template match<bound>(*op.a.get(), state) &&
682  b.template match<bound | bindings<A>::mask>(*op.b.get(), state));
683  }
684 
685  template<uint32_t bound, typename Op2, typename A2, typename B2>
686  HALIDE_ALWAYS_INLINE bool match(const BinOp<Op2, A2, B2> &op, MatcherState &state) const noexcept {
687  return (std::is_same<Op, Op2>::value &&
688  a.template match<bound>(unwrap(op.a), state) &&
689  b.template match<bound | bindings<A>::mask>(unwrap(op.b), state));
690  }
691 
692  constexpr static bool foldable = A::foldable && B::foldable;
693 
694  HALIDE_ALWAYS_INLINE
695  void make_folded_const(halide_scalar_value_t &val, halide_type_t &ty, MatcherState &state) const noexcept {
696  halide_scalar_value_t val_a, val_b;
697  if (std::is_same<A, IntLiteral>::value) {
698  b.make_folded_const(val_b, ty, state);
699  if ((std::is_same<Op, And>::value && val_b.u.u64 == 0) ||
700  (std::is_same<Op, Or>::value && val_b.u.u64 == 1)) {
701  // Short circuit
702  val = val_b;
703  return;
704  }
705  const uint16_t l = ty.lanes;
706  a.make_folded_const(val_a, ty, state);
707  ty.lanes |= l; // Make sure the overflow bits are sticky
708  } else {
709  a.make_folded_const(val_a, ty, state);
710  if ((std::is_same<Op, And>::value && val_a.u.u64 == 0) ||
711  (std::is_same<Op, Or>::value && val_a.u.u64 == 1)) {
712  // Short circuit
713  val = val_a;
714  return;
715  }
716  const uint16_t l = ty.lanes;
717  b.make_folded_const(val_b, ty, state);
718  ty.lanes |= l;
719  }
720  switch (ty.code) {
721  case halide_type_int:
722  val.u.i64 = constant_fold_bin_op<Op>(ty, val_a.u.i64, val_b.u.i64);
723  break;
724  case halide_type_uint:
725  val.u.u64 = constant_fold_bin_op<Op>(ty, val_a.u.u64, val_b.u.u64);
726  break;
727  case halide_type_float:
728  case halide_type_bfloat:
729  val.u.f64 = constant_fold_bin_op<Op>(ty, val_a.u.f64, val_b.u.f64);
730  break;
731  default:
732  // unreachable
733  ;
734  }
735  }
736 
737  HALIDE_ALWAYS_INLINE
738  Expr make(MatcherState &state, halide_type_t type_hint) const noexcept {
739  Expr ea, eb;
740  if (std::is_same<A, IntLiteral>::value) {
741  eb = b.make(state, type_hint);
742  ea = a.make(state, eb.type());
743  } else {
744  ea = a.make(state, type_hint);
745  eb = b.make(state, ea.type());
746  }
747  // We sometimes mix vectors and scalars in the rewrite rules,
748  // so insert a broadcast if necessary.
749  if (ea.type().is_vector() && !eb.type().is_vector()) {
750  eb = Broadcast::make(eb, ea.type().lanes());
751  }
752  if (eb.type().is_vector() && !ea.type().is_vector()) {
753  ea = Broadcast::make(ea, eb.type().lanes());
754  }
755  return Op::make(std::move(ea), std::move(eb));
756  }
757 };

768 // Matches one of the comparison operators
769 template<typename Op, typename A, typename B>
770 struct CmpOp {
771  struct pattern_tag {};
772  A a;
773  B b;
774 
775  constexpr static uint32_t binds = bindings<A>::mask | bindings<B>::mask;
776 
777  constexpr static IRNodeType min_node_type = Op::_node_type;
778  constexpr static IRNodeType max_node_type = Op::_node_type;
779  constexpr static bool canonical = (A::canonical &&
780  B::canonical &&
781  (!commutative(Op::_node_type) || A::max_node_type >= B::min_node_type) &&
782  (Op::_node_type != IRNodeType::GE) &&
783  (Op::_node_type != IRNodeType::GT));
784 
785  template<uint32_t bound>
786  HALIDE_ALWAYS_INLINE bool match(const BaseExprNode &e, MatcherState &state) const noexcept {
787  if (e.node_type != Op::_node_type) {
788  return false;
789  }
790  const Op &op = (const Op &)e;
791  return (a.template match<bound>(*op.a.get(), state) &&
792  b.template match<bound | bindings<A>::mask>(*op.b.get(), state));
793  }
794 
795  template<uint32_t bound, typename Op2, typename A2, typename B2>
796  HALIDE_ALWAYS_INLINE bool match(const CmpOp<Op2, A2, B2> &op, MatcherState &state) const noexcept {
797  return (std::is_same<Op, Op2>::value &&
798  a.template match<bound>(unwrap(op.a), state) &&
799  b.template match<bound | bindings<A>::mask>(unwrap(op.b), state));
800  }
801 
802  constexpr static bool foldable = A::foldable && B::foldable;
803 
804  HALIDE_ALWAYS_INLINE
805  void make_folded_const(halide_scalar_value_t &val, halide_type_t &ty, MatcherState &state) const noexcept {
806  halide_scalar_value_t val_a, val_b;
807  // If one side is an untyped const, evaluate the other side first to get a type hint.
808  if (std::is_same<A, IntLiteral>::value) {
809  b.make_folded_const(val_b, ty, state);
810  const uint16_t l = ty.lanes;
811  a.make_folded_const(val_a, ty, state);
812  ty.lanes |= l;
813  } else {
814  a.make_folded_const(val_a, ty, state);
815  const uint16_t l = ty.lanes;
816  b.make_folded_const(val_b, ty, state);
817  ty.lanes |= l;
818  }
819  switch (ty.code) {
820  case halide_type_int:
821  val.u.u64 = constant_fold_cmp_op<Op>(val_a.u.i64, val_b.u.i64);
822  break;
823  case halide_type_uint:
824  val.u.u64 = constant_fold_cmp_op<Op>(val_a.u.u64, val_b.u.u64);
825  break;
826  case halide_type_float:
827  case halide_type_bfloat:
828  val.u.u64 = constant_fold_cmp_op<Op>(val_a.u.f64, val_b.u.f64);
829  break;
830  default:
831  // unreachable
832  ;
833  }
834  ty.code = halide_type_uint;
835  ty.bits = 1;
836  }
837 
838  HALIDE_ALWAYS_INLINE
839  Expr make(MatcherState &state, halide_type_t type_hint) const {
840  // If one side is an untyped const, evaluate the other side first to get a type hint.
841  Expr ea, eb;
842  if (std::is_same<A, IntLiteral>::value) {
843  eb = b.make(state, {});
844  ea = a.make(state, eb.type());
845  } else {
846  ea = a.make(state, {});
847  eb = b.make(state, ea.type());
848  }
849  // We sometimes mix vectors and scalars in the rewrite rules,
850  // so insert a broadcast if necessary.
851  if (ea.type().is_vector() && !eb.type().is_vector()) {
852  eb = Broadcast::make(eb, ea.type().lanes());
853  }
854  if (eb.type().is_vector() && !ea.type().is_vector()) {
855  ea = Broadcast::make(ea, eb.type().lanes());
856  }
857  return Op::make(std::move(ea), std::move(eb));
858  }
859 };

965 template<>
966 HALIDE_ALWAYS_INLINE int64_t constant_fold_bin_op<Add>(halide_type_t &t, int64_t a, int64_t b) noexcept {
967  t.lanes |= ((t.bits >= 32) && add_would_overflow(t.bits, a, b)) ? MatcherState::signed_integer_overflow : 0;
968  int dead_bits = 64 - t.bits;
969  // Drop the high bits then sign-extend them back
970  return int64_t((uint64_t(a) + uint64_t(b)) << dead_bits) >> dead_bits;
971 }

975  uint64_t ones = (uint64_t)(-1);
976  return (a + b) & (ones >> (64 - t.bits));
977 }

1375 template<typename... Args>
1376 struct Intrin {
1377  struct pattern_tag {};
1378  Call::IntrinsicOp intrin;
1379  std::tuple<Args...> args;
1380 
1381  static constexpr uint32_t binds = bitwise_or_reduce((bindings<Args>::mask)...);
1382 
1383  constexpr static IRNodeType min_node_type = IRNodeType::Call;
1384  constexpr static IRNodeType max_node_type = IRNodeType::Call;
1385  constexpr static bool canonical = and_reduce((Args::canonical)...);
1386 
1387  template<int i,
1388  uint32_t bound,
1389  typename = typename std::enable_if<(i < sizeof...(Args))>::type>
1390  HALIDE_ALWAYS_INLINE bool match_args(int, const Call &c, MatcherState &state) const noexcept {
1391  using T = decltype(std::get<i>(args));
1392  return (std::get<i>(args).template match<bound>(*c.args[i].get(), state) &&
1393  match_args<i + 1, bound | bindings<T>::mask>(0, c, state));
1394  }
1395 
1396  template<int i, uint32_t binds>
1397  HALIDE_ALWAYS_INLINE bool match_args(double, const Call &c, MatcherState &state) const noexcept {
1398  return true;
1399  }
1400 
1401  template<uint32_t bound>
1402  HALIDE_ALWAYS_INLINE bool match(const BaseExprNode &e, MatcherState &state) const noexcept {
1403  if (e.node_type != IRNodeType::Call) {
1404  return false;
1405  }
1406  const Call &c = (const Call &)e;
1407  return (c.is_intrinsic(intrin) && match_args<0, bound>(0, c, state));
1408  }
1409 
1410  template<int i,
1411  typename = typename std::enable_if<(i < sizeof...(Args))>::type>
1412  HALIDE_ALWAYS_INLINE void print_args(int, std::ostream &s) const {
1413  s << std::get<i>(args);
1414  if (i + 1 < sizeof...(Args)) {
1415  s << ", ";
1416  }
1417  print_args<i + 1>(0, s);
1418  }
1419 
1420  template<int i>
1421  HALIDE_ALWAYS_INLINE void print_args(double, std::ostream &s) const {
1422  }
1423 
1424  HALIDE_ALWAYS_INLINE
1425  void print_args(std::ostream &s) const {
1426  print_args<0>(0, s);
1427  }
1428 
1429  HALIDE_ALWAYS_INLINE
1430  Expr make(MatcherState &state, halide_type_t type_hint) const {
1431  Expr arg0 = std::get<0>(args).make(state, type_hint);
1432  if (intrin == Call::likely) {
1433  return likely(arg0);
1434  } else if (intrin == Call::likely_if_innermost) {
1435  return likely_if_innermost(arg0);
1436  } else if (intrin == Call::abs) {
1437  return abs(arg0);
1438  }
1439 
1440  Expr arg1 = std::get<const_min(1, sizeof...(Args) - 1)>(args).make(state, type_hint);
1441  if (intrin == Call::absd) {
1442  return absd(arg0, arg1);
1443  } else if (intrin == Call::widening_add) {
1444  return widening_add(arg0, arg1);
1445  } else if (intrin == Call::widening_sub) {
1446  return widening_sub(arg0, arg1);
1447  } else if (intrin == Call::widening_mul) {
1448  return widening_mul(arg0, arg1);
1449  } else if (intrin == Call::saturating_add) {
1450  return saturating_add(arg0, arg1);
1451  } else if (intrin == Call::saturating_sub) {
1452  return saturating_sub(arg0, arg1);
1453  } else if (intrin == Call::halving_add) {
1454  return halving_add(arg0, arg1);
1455  } else if (intrin == Call::halving_sub) {
1456  return halving_sub(arg0, arg1);
1457  } else if (intrin == Call::rounding_halving_add) {
1458  return rounding_halving_add(arg0, arg1);
1459  } else if (intrin == Call::rounding_halving_sub) {
1460  return rounding_halving_sub(arg0, arg1);
1461  } else if (intrin == Call::shift_left) {
1462  return arg0 << arg1;
1463  } else if (intrin == Call::shift_right) {
1464  return arg0 >> arg1;
1465  } else if (intrin == Call::rounding_shift_left) {
1466  return rounding_shift_left(arg0, arg1);
1467  } else if (intrin == Call::rounding_shift_right) {
1468  return rounding_shift_right(arg0, arg1);
1469  }
1470 
1471  internal_error << "Unhandled intrinsic in IRMatcher: " << intrin;
1472  return Expr();
1473  }
1474 
1475  constexpr static bool foldable = false;
1476 
1477  HALIDE_ALWAYS_INLINE
1478  Intrin(Call::IntrinsicOp intrin, Args... args) noexcept
1479  : intrin(intrin), args(args...) {
1480  }
1481 };

1486  op.print_args(s);
1487  s << ")";

1489 }

1607 template<typename C, typename T, typename F>
1608 struct SelectOp {
1609  struct pattern_tag {};
1610  C c;
1611  T t;
1612  F f;
1613 
1614  constexpr static uint32_t binds = bindings<C>::mask | bindings<T>::mask | bindings<F>::mask;
1615 
1616  constexpr static IRNodeType min_node_type = IRNodeType::Select;
1617  constexpr static IRNodeType max_node_type = IRNodeType::Select;
1618 
1619  constexpr static bool canonical = C::canonical && T::canonical && F::canonical;
1620 
1621  template<uint32_t bound>
1622  HALIDE_ALWAYS_INLINE bool match(const BaseExprNode &e, MatcherState &state) const noexcept {
1623  if (e.node_type != Select::_node_type) {
1624  return false;
1625  }
1626  const Select &op = (const Select &)e;
1627  return (c.template match<bound>(*op.condition.get(), state) &&
1628  t.template match<bound | bindings<C>::mask>(*op.true_value.get(), state) &&
1629  f.template match<bound | bindings<C>::mask | bindings<T>::mask>(*op.false_value.get(), state));
1630  }
1631  template<uint32_t bound, typename C2, typename T2, typename F2>
1632  HALIDE_ALWAYS_INLINE bool match(const SelectOp<C2, T2, F2> &instance, MatcherState &state) const noexcept {
1633  return (c.template match<bound>(unwrap(instance.c), state) &&
1634  t.template match<bound | bindings<C>::mask>(unwrap(instance.t), state) &&
1635  f.template match<bound | bindings<C>::mask | bindings<T>::mask>(unwrap(instance.f), state));
1636  }
1637 
1638  HALIDE_ALWAYS_INLINE
1639  Expr make(MatcherState &state, halide_type_t type_hint) const {
1640  return Select::make(c.make(state, {}), t.make(state, type_hint), f.make(state, type_hint));
1641  }
1642 
1643  constexpr static bool foldable = C::foldable && T::foldable && F::foldable;
1644 
1645  template<typename C1 = C>
1646  HALIDE_ALWAYS_INLINE void make_folded_const(halide_scalar_value_t &val, halide_type_t &ty, MatcherState &state) const noexcept {
1647  halide_scalar_value_t c_val, t_val, f_val;
1648  halide_type_t c_ty;
1649  c.make_folded_const(c_val, c_ty, state);
1650  if ((c_val.u.u64 & 1) == 1) {
1651  t.make_folded_const(val, ty, state);
1652  } else {
1653  f.make_folded_const(val, ty, state);
1654  }
1655  ty.lanes |= c_ty.lanes & MatcherState::special_values_mask;
1656  }
1657 };

1673 template<typename A, typename B>
1674 struct BroadcastOp {
1675  struct pattern_tag {};
1676  A a;
1677  B lanes;
1678 
1679  constexpr static uint32_t binds = bindings<A>::mask | bindings<B>::mask;
1680 
1681  constexpr static IRNodeType min_node_type = IRNodeType::Broadcast;
1682  constexpr static IRNodeType max_node_type = IRNodeType::Broadcast;
1683 
1684  constexpr static bool canonical = A::canonical && B::canonical;
1685 
1686  template<uint32_t bound>
1687  HALIDE_ALWAYS_INLINE bool match(const BaseExprNode &e, MatcherState &state) const noexcept {
1688  if (e.node_type == Broadcast::_node_type) {
1689  const Broadcast &op = (const Broadcast &)e;
1690  if (a.template match<bound>(*op.value.get(), state) &&
1691  lanes.template match<bound>(op.lanes, state)) {
1692  return true;
1693  }
1694  }
1695  return false;
1696  }

1898  constexpr static IRNodeType max_node_type = IRNodeType::Sub;
1899

1903  HALIDE_ALWAYS_INLINE bool match(const BaseExprNode &e, MatcherState &state) const noexcept {
1904  if (e.node_type != Sub::_node_type) {
1905  return false;
1906  }

1913  HALIDE_ALWAYS_INLINE bool match(NegateOp<A2> &&p, MatcherState &state) const noexcept {
1914  return a.template match<bound>(unwrap(p.a), state);
1915  }
1916 
1917  HALIDE_ALWAYS_INLINE
1918  Expr make(MatcherState &state, halide_type_t type_hint) const {
1919  Expr ea = a.make(state, type_hint);
1920  Expr z = make_zero(ea.type());
1921  return Sub::make(std::move(z), std::move(ea));
1922  }
1923 
1924  constexpr static bool foldable = A::foldable;
1925 
1926  template<typename A1 = A>
1927  HALIDE_ALWAYS_INLINE void make_folded_const(halide_scalar_value_t &val, halide_type_t &ty, MatcherState &state) const noexcept {
1928  a.make_folded_const(val, ty, state);
1929  int dead_bits = 64 - ty.bits;
1930  switch (ty.code) {
1931  case halide_type_int:
1932  if (ty.bits >= 32 && val.u.u64 && (val.u.u64 << (65 - ty.bits)) == 0) {
1933  // Trying to negate the most negative signed int for a no-overflow type.
1934  ty.lanes |= MatcherState::signed_integer_overflow;
1935  } else {
1936  // Negate, drop the high bits, and then sign-extend them back
1937  val.u.i64 = int64_t(uint64_t(-val.u.i64) << dead_bits) >> dead_bits;
1938  }
1939  break;
1940  case halide_type_uint:
1941  val.u.u64 = ((-val.u.u64) << dead_bits) >> dead_bits;
1942  break;
1943  case halide_type_float:
1944  case halide_type_bfloat:
1945  val.u.f64 = -val.u.f64;
1946  break;
1947  default:
1948  // unreachable
1949  ;
1950  }
1951  }
1952 };

2454 // Verify properties of each rewrite rule. Currently just fuzz tests them.
2455 template<typename Before,
2456  typename After,
2457  typename Predicate,
2458  typename = typename std::enable_if<std::decay<Before>::type::foldable &&
2459  std::decay<After>::type::foldable>::type>
2460 HALIDE_NEVER_INLINE void fuzz_test_rule(Before &&before, After &&after, Predicate &&pred,
2461  halide_type_t wildcard_type, halide_type_t output_type) noexcept {
2462 
2463  // We only validate the rules in the scalar case
2464  wildcard_type.lanes = output_type.lanes = 1;
2465 
2466  // Track which types this rule has been tested for before
2467  static std::set<uint32_t> tested;
2468 
2469  if (!tested.insert(reinterpret_bits<uint32_t>(wildcard_type)).second) {
2470  return;
2471  }
2472 
2473  // Print it in a form where it can be piped into a python/z3 validator
2474  debug(0) << "validate('" << before << "', '" << after << "', '" << pred << "', " << Type(wildcard_type) << ", " << Type(output_type) << ")\n";
2475 
2476  // Substitute some random constants into the before and after
2477  // expressions and see if the rule holds true. This should catch
2478  // silly errors, but not necessarily corner cases.
2479  static std::mt19937_64 rng(0);
2480  MatcherState state;
2481 
2482  Expr exprs[max_wild];
2483 
2484  for (int trials = 0; trials < 100; trials++) {
2485  // We want to test small constants more frequently than
2486  // large ones, otherwise we'll just get coverage of
2487  // overflow rules.
2488  int shift = (int)(rng() & (wildcard_type.bits - 1));
2489 
2490  for (int i = 0; i < max_wild; i++) {
2491  // Bind all the exprs and constants
2492  switch (wildcard_type.code) {
2493  case halide_type_uint: {
2494  // Normalize to the type's range by adding zero
2495  uint64_t val = constant_fold_bin_op<Add>(wildcard_type, (uint64_t)rng() >> shift, 0);
2496  state.set_bound_const(i, val, wildcard_type);
2497  val = constant_fold_bin_op<Add>(wildcard_type, (uint64_t)rng() >> shift, 0);
2498  exprs[i] = make_const(wildcard_type, val);
2499  state.set_binding(i, *exprs[i].get());
2500  } break;
2501  case halide_type_int: {
2502  int64_t val = constant_fold_bin_op<Add>(wildcard_type, (int64_t)rng() >> shift, 0);
2503  state.set_bound_const(i, val, wildcard_type);
2504  val = constant_fold_bin_op<Add>(wildcard_type, (int64_t)rng() >> shift, 0);
2505  exprs[i] = make_const(wildcard_type, val);
2506  } break;
2507  case halide_type_float:
2508  case halide_type_bfloat: {
2509  // Use a very narrow range of precise floats, so
2510  // that none of the rules a human is likely to
2511  // write have instabilities.
2512  double val = ((int64_t)(rng() & 15) - 8) / 2.0;
2513  state.set_bound_const(i, val, wildcard_type);
2514  val = ((int64_t)(rng() & 15) - 8) / 2.0;
2515  exprs[i] = make_const(wildcard_type, val);
2516  } break;
2517  default:
2518  return; // Don't care about handles
2519  }
2520  state.set_binding(i, *exprs[i].get());
2521  }
2522 
2523  halide_scalar_value_t val_pred, val_before, val_after;
2524  halide_type_t type = output_type;
2525  if (!evaluate_predicate(pred, state)) {
2526  continue;
2527  }
2528  before.make_folded_const(val_before, type, state);
2529  uint16_t lanes = type.lanes;
2530  after.make_folded_const(val_after, type, state);
2531  lanes |= type.lanes;
2532 
2533  if (lanes & MatcherState::special_values_mask) {
2534  continue;
2535  }
2536 
2537  bool ok = true;
2538  switch (output_type.code) {
2539  case halide_type_uint:
2540  // Compare normalized representations
2541  ok &= (constant_fold_bin_op<Add>(output_type, val_before.u.u64, 0) ==
2542  constant_fold_bin_op<Add>(output_type, val_after.u.u64, 0));
2543  break;
2544  case halide_type_int:
2545  ok &= (constant_fold_bin_op<Add>(output_type, val_before.u.i64, 0) ==
2546  constant_fold_bin_op<Add>(output_type, val_after.u.i64, 0));
2547  break;
2548  case halide_type_float:
2549  case halide_type_bfloat: {
2550  double error = std::abs(val_before.u.f64 - val_after.u.f64);
2551  // We accept an equal bit pattern (e.g. inf vs inf),
2552  // a small floating point difference, or turning a nan into not-a-nan.
2553  ok &= (error < 0.01 ||
2554  val_before.u.u64 == val_after.u.u64 ||
2555  std::isnan(val_before.u.f64));
2556  break;
2557  }
2558  default:
2559  return;
2560  }
2561 
2562  if (!ok) {
2563  debug(0) << "Fails with values:\n";
2564  for (int i = 0; i < max_wild; i++) {
2565  halide_scalar_value_t val;
2566  state.get_bound_const(i, val, wildcard_type);
2567  debug(0) << " c" << i << ": " << make_const_expr(val, wildcard_type) << "\n";
2568  }
2569  for (int i = 0; i < max_wild; i++) {
2570  debug(0) << " _" << i << ": " << Expr(state.get_binding(i)) << "\n";
2571  }
2572  debug(0) << " Before: " << make_const_expr(val_before, output_type) << "\n";
2573  debug(0) << " After: " << make_const_expr(val_after, output_type) << "\n";
2574  debug(0) << val_before.u.u64 << " " << val_after.u.u64 << "\n";
2575  internal_error;
2576  }
2577  }
2578 }

2584  std::decay<After>::type::foldable)>::type>
2585 HALIDE_ALWAYS_INLINE void fuzz_test_rule(Before &&before, After &&after, Predicate &&pred,

2595 template<typename Pattern,

2597 HALIDE_ALWAYS_INLINE bool evaluate_predicate(Pattern p, MatcherState &state) {

2640  static_assert((Before::binds & After::binds) == After::binds, "Rule result uses unbound values");
2641  static_assert(Before::canonical, "LHS of rewrite rule should be in canonical form");
2642  static_assert(After::canonical, "RHS of rewrite rule should be in canonical form");
2643 #if HALIDE_FUZZ_TEST_RULES

2646  if (before.template match<0>(unwrap(instance), state)) {
2647 #if HALIDE_DEBUG_MATCHED_RULES

2649 #endif
2650  build_replacement(after);
2651  return true;
2652  } else {
2653 #if HALIDE_DEBUG_UNMATCHED_RULES
2654  debug(0) << instance << " does not match " << before << "\n";
2655 #endif
2656  return false;
2657  }
2658  }

2779 /** Construct a rewriter for the given instance, which may be a pattern
2780  * with concrete expressions as leaves, or just an expression. The
2781  * second optional argument (wildcard_type) is a hint as to what the
2782  * type of the wildcards is likely to be. If omitted it uses the same
2783  * type as the expression itself. They are not required to be this
2784  * type, but the rule will only be tested for wildcards of that type
2785  * when testing is enabled.
2786  *
2787  * The rewriter can be used to check to see if the instance is one of
2788  * some number of patterns and if so rewrite it into another form,
2789  * using its operator() method. See Simplify.cpp for a bunch of
2790  * example usage.
2791  *
2792  * Important: Any Exprs in patterns are captured by reference, not by
2793  * value, so ensure they outlive the rewriter.
2794  */
2795 // @{
